The recipes truly are idea for today's heat - we couldn't have planned better! Turning on your stove or oven would just make it hotter, these no cook recipes will blow you away and keep you cool all summer long.

Red Pepper Pasta, AKA "Peperonata" is an awesome way to switch up your pasta game this summer - full recipe is written on substack if you follow the like in my bio #pastatime

Is mammamia one word? or is it mamma mia? anyways, this rich, smooth, juicy and spicy pomodoro sauce will have you screaming the aformentioned word/phrase #nightimtenoodles rice is available on my substack in my bio

Did you know that one of Venice's classic regional dishes is anchovy and onion sauce? They simply call it "salsa" Bigoli are fat spaghetti, like bucatini sans the hole running through the center. Any larger format twirly pasta will do. Good anchovies make this dish sing as opposed to stinking. recipe in my substack follow link in the bio! #pastatime

I went to Italy with my dad for the first time in 2001 - I ordered my pasta "al dente". With my hi-8 camera in hand, I captured the moment on tape, not that I'd ever forget this moment with my dad. I learned my lesson, al dente goes without saying, even though I was just trying to say as many words in italian as possible to impress Dino. 
thank you Dino for this, wherever you are.

Need knife skills? This one is called the "up & down". it's all about not recoiling too far with the knife and using the other hand as a guide. Five years, an Emmy Award and nearly 1,500 hours on set, we’re here at 100 episodes! I’m so grateful for this opportunity - and I’m reminded daily by the people I work with. @tastemade took a risk on me and tried 5 concepts before this one, the road ain’t always straight! Thanks tastemade. @fluidframe has helped me become the freest version of myself on camera, which isn’t something that can happen in a week. It happens over months and years, serious conversations, heavy moments in the middle of work and uplifting ones right when the day has wrapped. Thank you LJ and David, and Hannah, Tara, Erin, Courtney, Jay, Jim, Sade and so many more. If you’re reading this and trying to find your own path, I’m in year 14 and there were 8 years of pain before it started working a little bit. Secondly, it’s way more fun to have fun than be so serious. Struggle Meals is fun, I hope you have fun doing whatever you do too - thank you for watching!! 100 more?  Tune in Thursday on Tastemade, wherever you stream free!
Food for thought, to all those bakers out there who love it because of “the precision”. Pass this along.
